id: pm-j3swnb
title: Relationship timestamp snapshots must honor event time for late and offline arrivals
description: "RelationshipEventLog.snapshot({atTimestamp}) currently chooses an append prefix ending at the last event whose timestamp is <= the target. If a later-appended offline event has an older event-time, the prefix can include earlier-appended events whose timestamps are after the requested instant. Point-in-time reconstruction must filter all immutable events by event time while preserving append order among included events."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: "area:graph","area:sdk",event-sourcing,offline-first,temporal
created_at: "2026-07-23T10:17:49.204Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T11:27:44.770Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-23T11:26:59.113Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: "Timestamp snapshots exclude every event after the requested event-time regardless of append order; late and offline arrivals remain visible at their actual event-time; version snapshots and current snapshots retain append-sequence semantics; regression tests cover add, supersede, remove, empty, and out-of-order streams; SDK docs state append-time versus event-time semantics"
parent: pm-usfg
severity: high
resolution: "RelationshipEventLog timestamp snapshots now filter every immutable event by event time, preserve append order among included events, and report the highest included append sequence."
expected_result: "Timestamp snapshots materialize exactly the relationships effective from events at or before the requested instant, including late arrivals and excluding future-dated events."
actual_result: Late and offline events appear at their true event time; future-dated events are excluded even when appended earlier; current/version snapshots retain append semantics; regression and full coverage gates pass.
component: src/sdk/relationship-history.ts
